history.content:
Hi there,

I'm afraid I'm not sure what you mean by "will it still count for graduation?". All requirements must be passed to be fulfilled. This means that if you need it to graduate (because you haven't yet fulfilled that breadth, don't have 36 upper division units, etc), you will not be able to graduate with a NP.

children.subject: Ah okay. Yeah I'm kind of worried about the breadth but I guess there's not much I can do about the requirements.

history.content: I'm a graduating CS major and taking my last breadth requirement P/NP. If I NP the class, does it still count towards graduation? I know I won't get units for NP-ing it but I'm taking more important classes and just don't have enough time to learn all the material. Also, how does this look in terms of graduate admissions?
history.subject: NP a breadth class
